snippet: French Open champion Garbine Muguruza jumped two spots to a career-high No. 2 in the WTA rankings on Monday, while runner-up Serena Williams remained at No. 1, where she's been for more than three years....
lead_paragraph: French Open champion Garbine Muguruza jumped two spots to a career-high No. 2 in the WTA rankings on Monday, while runner-up Serena Williams remained at No. 1, where she's been for more than three years.

headline.print_headline: Muguruza Rises to No. 2, Behind Williams, After French Title
headline.main: Muguruza Rises to No. 2, Behind Williams, After French Title
